HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 29
By Terry
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Oakland High
School football team, TSSAA Division I, Class
6A state champion.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Oakland High School football team achieved an extraordinary level of
success during the 2024 season, winning the coveted Tennessee Secondary School Athletic
Association (TSSAA) Division I, Class 6A State Football Championship; and
WHEREAS, the Oakland Patriots claimed the title of state champion by defeating
Houston High School in a hard-fought battle by a score of 42-20 in the BlueCross Bowl
championship game on December 7, 2024, at Finley Stadium in Chattanooga; and
WHEREAS, on their path to the championship game, the Patriots defeated Lebanon 41-
0, Mt. Juliet 35-28, archrival Riverdale 49-46, and Maryville 21-13, before their final victory over
Houston to secure the right to hoist the iconic gold football trophy; and
WHEREAS, the 2024 Oakland Patriots enjoyed the services of an outstanding coaching
staff led by Head Coach Kevin Creasy, who instilled in these exceptional young men a
commitment to excellence in all that they do and encouraged maximum effort on the football
field; and
WHEREAS, state championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication, and
the ability to work together as a team and excel with a cooperative spirit; the Patriots exhibited
each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
